Class DiscoveryDocument

Manages a JSON-formatted document from the experimental Google Discovery API version 0.1.

Warning: this is based on an undocumented experimental Google API that may stop working or change in behavior at any time. Beware of this risk if running this in production code.

Warning: in prior version 1.2 there was a {@code load(String)} method. Instead, you should now use GoogleApi.load().

@since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class GoogleApi, HttpTransport transport

HTTP transport required for building requests in .buildRequest(String, Object). It is initialized using GoogleTransport.create().
Class JsonCContent

Serializes JSON-C content based on the data key/value mapping object for an item, wrapped in a {@code "data"} envelope.

Sample usage: 

 
  static void setContent(HttpRequest request, Object data) {
     JsonCContent content = new JsonCContent();
    content.jsonFactory = new JacksonFactory();
    content.data = data;
     request.content = content;
  }
@since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class JsonCParser

Parses HTTP JSON-C response content into an data class of key/value pairs, assuming the data is wrapped in a {@code "data"} envelope.

Sample usage: 

 
  static void setParser(GoogleTransportHttpTransport transport) {
   transport.addParser( JsonCParser parser = new JsonCParser();
    parser.jsonFactory = new JacksonFactory();
    transport.addParser(parser);
  }
@since 1.0 @author Yaniv Inbar
Class JsonCParser, JsonParser parserForResponse(JsonFactory, HttpResponse)

Returns a JSON parser to use for parsing the given HTTP response, skipped over the {@code "data"} envelope.

The parser will be closed if any throwable is thrown. The current token will be the value of the {@code "data"} key.

Upgrade warning: prior to version 1.3, there was no {@code jsonFactory} parameter, but now it is required.

@param response HTTP response @return JSON parser @throws IllegalArgumentException if content type is not Json.CONTENT_TYPE or if {@code "data"} key is not found @throws IOException I/O exceptionexception @since 1.3
